  "prompt": "Is low-income a good college essay topic?",
  "response": "Writing about low-income experiences can be a good college essay topic if approached thoughtfully. Here are some pros and cons:\n\nPros:\n- Shows personal resilience and overcoming challenges\n- Demonstrates perspective and personal growth\n- Can highlight unique life experiences\n- Provides context for academic achievements\n- Helps admissions understand your background\n\nCons:\n- Can feel like a clich\u00e9 if not handled uniquely\n- Might come across as seeking pity if not written carefully\n- Could potentially reinforce stereotypes\n\nTips for writing effectively:\n- Focus on your personal strengths and growth\n- Highlight specific experiences, not just general hardship\n- Emphasize how you've overcome challenges\n- Show your character, determination, and perspective\n- Avoid a purely narrative \"sad story\" approach\n- Connect your experiences to your goals and aspirations\n\nThe key is to write a compelling, authentic narrative that reveals something meaningful about you beyond just your economic background. The essay should showcase your character, resilience, and potential, not just describe financial struggles.\n\nWould you like help brainstorming how to approach this topic?",
